\pard\qc\b Installation and Setup Guide\b0\par
\pard\qc Project: StoryBuddy / AweTales - Conversational Voice AI Assistant\par
\pard\qc Task ID: AWE_T1\par
\par
\pard\b Problem Statement\b0\par
\b Title:\b0 End-to-End Real-Time Conversational Voice AI Pipeline\par
\par
The objective of this project is to design and implement a real-time conversational AI system that accepts live voice input, preprocesses audio, converts speech to text, understands user intent using a Large Language Model, retrieves relevant context using Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG), and returns a meaningful conversational response with optional speech output.\par
\par
\b System Overview\b0\par
The implemented pipeline is:\par
\par
Microphone Input -> Audio Capture/Streaming -> Audio Preprocessing (noise reduction + silence handling) -> Speech Recognition (Whisper) -> Knowledge Retrieval (FAISS + knowledge.txt) -> LLM Reasoning (Groq) -> Text Response (and optional TTS audio)\par
\par
\b Prerequisites\b0\par
Install the following before running the project:\par
\par
1. Python 3.9 or higher\par
2. Git\par
3. FFmpeg (required for Whisper audio processing)\par
\par
\b Step 1: Clone the Repository\b0\par
git clone https://github.com/navyabokam/StoryBuddy_AweTales.git\par
cd StoryBuddy_AweTales\par
\par
\b Step 2: Install Required Dependencies\b0\par
pip install -r requirements.txt\par
\par
This installs required libraries including Flask, Whisper, OpenAI SDK (Groq-compatible), FAISS, LangChain, audio processing libraries, and related dependencies.\par
\par
\b Step 3: Configure Environment Variables\b0\par
Create a file named .env in the project root and add:\par
\par
GROK_API_KEY=your_api_key_here\par
APP_SECRET=your_secret_here\par
\par
Optional:\par
WHISPER_MODEL=tiny\par
ENABLE_ASR_WARMUP=0\par
FLASK_DEBUG=0\par
\par
\b Step 4: Run the Application\b0\par
Run the Flask backend:\par
python main.py\par
\par
Open in browser:\par
http://127.0.0.1:8000\par
\par
\b Step 5: Application Workflow\b0\par
1. Click Start Talking (microphone button).\par
2. Speak your query clearly.\par
3. The system captures and preprocesses audio.\par
4. Speech is converted to text using Whisper ASR.\par
5. Context is retrieved from the knowledge base (knowledge.txt) using FAISS-based RAG.\par
6. Query + context are sent to Groq LLM for response generation.\par
7. The generated response is shown in chat and stored in session history.\par
8. Optional server-side TTS can return spoken output audio.\par
\par
\b Demo Link\b0\par
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1PWasDh7uJk5frgo7tENIdbFNFXCSF13n/view?usp=sharing\par
\par
\b Project Repository\b0\par
https://github.com/navyabokam/StoryBuddy_AweTales.git\par
\par
\b Notes\b0\par
1. Main implementation runs through main.py (Flask web app).\par
2. app.py is an older Streamlit-based version retained for reference.\par
3. Ensure FFmpeg is correctly added to system PATH before running.\par
}
